In this statement, the author, on behalf of the American people, wishes all Muslims a joyful Ramadan. They acknowledge that during this month of fasting, Muslims find meaning and inspiration in acts of charity and meditation that strengthen communities. The author emphasizes the importance of rejecting violence, pursuing peace, and helping those in need. They condemn recent terrorist attacks in the United Kingdom and Egypt, stating that such acts only strengthen their resolve to defeat terrorists and their ideology. The author also mentions their recent visit to Saudi Arabia, where they met with leaders of Muslim nations to promote peace and security. They reiterate America's commitment to standing with partners against terrorism. The author extends their best wishes to Muslims worldwide for a blessed month of observing Ramadan traditions.